PN,30801
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1784017089
OL,3,C2,700 deaths linked to May and June
OL,4,Cheatwaves as climate change impacts UK
OL,6,FMore than 2,700 people died from heat-
OL,7,Frelated causes during May and June's
OL,8,Frecord hot spells, experts have
OL,9,Festimated.
OL,11,FResearchers from Imperial College
OL,12,FLondon, the Met Office, and the London
OL,13,FSchool of Hygiene and Tropical
OL,14,FMedicine (LSHTM) found that climate
OL,15,Fchange significantly drove up the
OL,16,Fdeath toll, as more than two fifths
OL,17,F(42%) died as a result of the extra
OL,18,Fheat caused by human activity ` mostly
OL,19,Fburning fossil fuels.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1784017089
OL,3,C2,700 deaths linked to May and June
OL,4,Cheatwaves as climate change impacts UK
OL,6,FTheir study examined the periods
OL,7,Faround the record-breaking heatwaves
OL,8,Fof May, when temperatures peaked at
OL,9,F35.1C, and June, which hit new highs
OL,10,Ffor the month of above 37C,
OL,11,Faccompanied by high humidity.
OL,13,FThe analysis used weather data,
OL,14,Fclimate models and heat-related deaths
OL,15,Fresearch to estimate the number of
OL,16,Fpeople who died in the heatwaves, and
OL,17,Fcompare it to how many lives would
OL,18,Fhave been lost in a climate that had
OL,19,Fnot been warmed by human activities.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1784017089
OL,3,C2,700 deaths linked to May and June
OL,4,Cheatwaves as climate change impacts UK
OL,6,FThe analysis found that about 550
OL,7,Fpeople are estimated to have died
OL,8,Fbecause of heat-related causes in nine
OL,9,Fdays of the May heatwave, and about
OL,10,F2,200 in the 11 days around the June
OL,11,Fheatwave in England and Wales.
OL,13,FAround 59% of the deaths in May, some
OL,14,F327 people, and 38%, some 825 people,
OL,15,Fof those in June could be attributed
OL,16,Fto the extra heat caused by climate
OL,17,Fchange, they found.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1784017089
OL,3,C2,700 deaths linked to May and June
OL,4,Cheatwaves as climate change impacts UK
OL,6,FThe researchers warn maximum daytime
OL,7,Ftemperatures are around 3C-4C hotter
OL,8,Fthan they would be without climate
OL,9,Fchange, raising the risks from the
OL,10,Fheat.
OL,12,FHigh temperatures are associated with
OL,13,Frisks including heat exhaustion, heat
OL,14,Fstroke, stress on the heart and
OL,15,Fkidneys and worsening chronic
OL,16,Fconditions such as heart disease, lung
OL,17,Fconditions and diabetes.
OL,19,FThey also worsen mental health,
OL,20,Fviolence and increase the risk of
OL,21,Fdeath from drowning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1784017089
OL,3,C2,700 deaths linked to May and June
OL,4,Cheatwaves as climate change impacts UK
OL,6,FThe Met Office's Dr Mark McCarthy
OL,7,Fdescribed the two record-breaking
OL,8,Fheatwaves as "exceptional".
OL,10,FHe said heatwave thresholds were
OL,11,Frarely met in May, but this year
OL,12,Fdaytime temperatures were widely 15C
OL,13,Fabove the average for the month in
OL,14,FEngland and Wales, while night-time
OL,15,Ftemperature records were also set.
OL,17,FThe June heatwave, which saw red
OL,18,Fwarnings for extreme heat issued on
OL,19,Fconsecutive days, was notable for its
OL,20,Fhumidity as well as heat, he said.
OL,26,@pD@NOUpD@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1784017089
OL,3,C2,700 deaths linked to May and June
OL,4,Cheatwaves as climate change impacts UK
OL,6,F"They were extreme heatwaves for the
OL,7,FUK and for all parts of western
OL,8,FEurope, and they're particularly
OL,9,Fexceptional for the timing and how
OL,10,Fearly in the year they occurred.
OL,12,F"This combination of extreme daytime
OL,13,Fheat, high humidity and hot nights all
OL,14,Fact to really contribute and increase
OL,15,Fthe impact these heatwaves have on our
OL,16,Finfrastructure, on transport,
OL,17,Fagriculture and particularly on our
OL,18,Fhealth and well being," he said.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOUzD@WO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1784017089
OL,3,C2,700 deaths linked to May and June
OL,4,Cheatwaves as climate change impacts UK
OL,6,FIt was clear climate change is making
OL,7,Fheatwaves more frequent and intense,
OL,8,Fhe said.Dr Clair Barnes from Imperial
OL,9,FCollege London, said heatwaves are the
OL,10,F"most dangerous kind of extreme
OL,11,Fweather", with the World Health
OL,12,FOrganisation recommending authorities
OL,13,Fin Europe plan for extreme heat in the
OL,14,Fsame way they do for winter flu.
OL,16,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,17,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,18,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,19,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,26,@rD@AOUsD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
